  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Both left single lung ventilation by left double lumen tube and bilateral ventilation with
      selective blockage of right middle lower lobe by bronchial blocker can provide suitable
      surgical field for minimally invasive cardiac surgery. The current study was designed to
      compare the impact of these two different methods on oxygenation, degree of pulmonary
      collapse and postoperative complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
